title: Lie bracket and commuting flows
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$X,Y \in \mathfrak X(M)$$ with local flows $$\theta$$ and $$\phi$$ respectively. Then $$[X,Y]=0$$ if and only if $$\theta_t \circ \phi_s = \phi_s \circ \theta_t$$ for all sufficiently small $$s$$ and $$t.$$